resourceList.title: React
resourceList.body: React is a JavaScript library for building user interfaces, particularly for creating single-page applications where user data can change without requiring a page reload. Developed and maintained by Facebook, React follows a component-based architecture, making it efficient for building interactive and reusable UI components.
resourceList.author: Jordan Walke

resourceList.title: Redux
resourceList.body: Redux is a state management library for JavaScript applications, often used with React. It provides a predictable state container, ensuring a consistent and manageable state for an application. Redux is commonly employed in larger applications to centralize and manage the state, making it easier to debug, test, and maintain complex UIs.
resourceList.author: Dan Abramov

resourceList.title: JavaScript
resourceList.body: JavaScript is a versatile, high-level programming language primarily used for front-end web development. It enables dynamic content on websites, enhancing user interactivity. JavaScript is also used on the server side (Node.js) and for building various applications beyond web development.
resourceList.author: Aderemi Opeyemi

resourceList.title: Express
resourceList.body: Express is a minimal and flexible web application framework for Node.js, designed to simplify the process of building robust and scalable web applications and APIs. It provides a set of features for web and mobile applications, making it easier to handle tasks such as routing, middleware integration, request handling, and response generation. With a simple and intuitive API, Express allows developers to create server-side logic effectively. It is widely used in the Node.js ecosystem and is known for its speed
resourceList.author: Daramola Afeez
